1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:09,280
Do you know that Mink likes you?

2
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,479
I know.

3
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,440
But you don't look at Pie
the way you look at your brother's wife.

4
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,160
What are you trying to stir up with me?

5
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:19,240
<i>Have you asked yourself</i>
<i>how you look at someone else's husband?</i>

6
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:22,480
A smart person like you should see

7
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,800
that you don't fit in with Pun's family,

8
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,000
but you're pushing through.

9
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:29,880
Seriously, are you happy
with how things are now?

10
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:33,920
I've got an appointment with Dr. Bee.

11
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,280
We'll discuss the IVF process tomorrow.

12
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,400
Have you ever been pregnant
or had a miscarriage?

13
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,920
I've had a miscarriage.

14
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,760
Please don't tell Pun
about my miscarriage yet.

15
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,920
I'll find a chance
to talk to him about it myself.

16
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:50,360
Go home! I said I'm going home. Now!

17
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,360
How can you stay calm about this?

18
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,800
It's like this isn't a big deal.

19
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:04,560
Pun.

20
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,320
You're grown up now.

21
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,480
You should understand me.

22
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,640
Understand what, Dad?

23
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:14,760
Understand you've been lying to us
and that you have another family?

24
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,160
Or now that I'm grown up,

25
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,440
I should just accept everything you do,
even if it's wrong?

26
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,760
Let me be clear, I don't understand.

27
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,200
I don't know how long
you've been lying to us.

28
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,960
But today, you have to make a choice.

29
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:27,920
You have to end this!

30
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,640
Pun.

31
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,600
I'm not choosing anything.

32
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,600
You see, I just had a baby with her.

33
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,480
How can I just leave her?

34
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:45,400
And I can't leave your mom either.

35
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,960
Do you think your mom
would just accept that?

36
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,120
Wait, Dad.

37
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,840
Why are you being so selfish?

38
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,040
Does that woman know?

39
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,400
Does she know about Mom and me?

40
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,240
She knows. She knows everything.

41
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,720
She knows, and she accepts it?

42
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,800
And this is the kind of person you chose?

43
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:16,000
I'm starting to doubt
what kind of person you are.

44
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,440
The dad I respected.

45
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,000
The dad I trusted.

46
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,680
The one who doesn't drink, doesn't smoke,

47
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:24,320
doesn't curse.

48
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,480
The one who practiced meditation,
who loved nature.

49
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:30,120
What was all that, Dad?!

50
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:32,520
Were you lying to me?

51
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,000
Were you just putting on an act?

52
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:38,200
Can I still trust you?

53
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,320
Pun.

54
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,000
I'm sorry.

55
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,440
It's useless, Dad.
You don't need to apologize.

56
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,520
Even if you apologize,
you're not fixing what you've done wrong.

57
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:03,800
You're still choosing to be selfish.

58
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,080
So why even apologize to me?

59
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:12,160
I'm sorry for disappointing you.

60
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,680
I'm so disappointed in you!

61
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:20,400
I never thought
you could do something like this.

62
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,720
You've made me feel like a fool.

63
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,800
Like you've been deceiving me
since I was a kid.

64
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,720
I'm not trying to make excuses.

65
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,600
But I never cheated on your mom before.

66
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,880
I've never done anything like this.

67
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:12,960
When you're as old as me,
you'll understand.

68
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,160
What do you want me to understand?

69
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:19,960
Understand that people can change.

70
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:24,600
The patience in a relationship
has its limits.

71
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,880
What we used to tolerate,

72
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,360
eventually we don't want to anymore.

73
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,920
When you don't want to tolerate it,
you have to find a way out!

74
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,280
By cheating?

75
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:41,040
By finding someone who values us more!

76
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:48,280
You know what your mom is like.

77
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:56,760
Before we got married,
I knew I was inferior to her in every way.

78
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,560
But because I loved her, I tolerated it.

79
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:06,440
I tolerated her pushing me down,
controlling me.

80
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,200
Over time, I couldn't take it anymore.

81
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:12,400
Then why didn't you talk to Mom?

82
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,120
Why didn't you communicate with her?

83
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,200
You can't use this reason to cheat on her.

84
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,360
I tried to talk to her.

85
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,120
But she wouldn't listen.

86
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,880
She never tried to adjust.

87
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,560
She's the way she is.

88
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,720
We can't change who she is.

89
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,600
You don't need to explain
anything anymore.

90
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,800
Your reasons don't make sense.

91
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,560
Then I won't say anything more.

92
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,560
When you're ready,

93
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,720
we'll have a heart-to-heart talk,
man to man.

94
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,280
Man to man?

95
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:49,080
Is what you're doing really manly?

96
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:52,800
Go ahead.

97
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,400
Do whatever makes you feel at ease.

98
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,040
If you want to think
or do something, go for it.

99
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,080
I know I've made a mistake.

100
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,880
I won't say anything more about it.

101
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,760
But there's just one thing I ask.

102
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:16,760
Keep this between us.
Don't let your mom find out.

103
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,840
You're saying it so easily.

104
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:27,400
If you want to make it hard,
go ahead and tell your mom.

105
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,880
But remember, Pun.

106
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:34,120
The person who will be hurt the most
is your mom.

107
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:38,760
Some things in life,
we don't need to know about.

108
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,039
Especially things that make us unhappy.

109
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:51,680
It's up to you now,
how you want to handle this.

110
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:36,080
22:03
FRIDAY 18TH AUGUST

111
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,400
Why are you coming home so late?

112
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,080
Where have you been?

113
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,600
Work.

114
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,520
Pie.

115
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,800
I'm asking you nicely.

116
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,200
I'm concerned.

117
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,760
Why are you answering me so bluntly?

118
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:51,480
At least I'm blunt,
not disappearing all day like you did.

119
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,840
I called, you didn't answer or call back.

120
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,240
Why should I speak nicely to you?

121
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,400
Why should I be the one
to explain everything gently?

122
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,440
It's not fair.

123
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,680
Why are you starting something with me?

124
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,040
I came home tired.
We should've talked nicely.

125
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,960
Don't act unreasonable like this.

126
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:07,480
Pun, I have my reasons.

127
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:10,120
Reasons you never ask about or listen to.

128
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,080
Then you assume I have no reasons.

129
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:13,480
Pie.

130
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:16,040
Seriously, what's going on?

131
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,960
Are you upset about something
and taking it out on me?

132
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:20,000
I haven't done anything to you.

133
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,040
I just asked where you've been.

134
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,800
Why are you getting so upset with me?

135
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,040
This is how you are, Pun.

136
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:27,240
It's always my fault. You're never wrong.

137
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,440
I haven't done anything to you.

138
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,040
I'm asking out of concern.
What did I do wrong?

139
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:32,960
Okay!

140
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:35,520
You're never wrong, Pun.
You're always right.

141
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,600
It's all my fault.
I'm the one who's wrong.

142
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,200
I'm no good, nothing good about me.

143
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,560
Stop with the sarcasm!

144
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,840
Are you looking for a fight?

145
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:45,080
I'm not being sarcastic.
I'm telling the truth.

146
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,440
I've never been good
in anyone's eyes here.

147
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,600
Stop!

148
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,640
Don't bring other people into this.

149
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,360
Who do you mean by "anyone here"?

150
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,160
You can't talk about my mom like that.

151
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,200
Yeah, I can't say anything about anyone!

152
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,960
But everyone has the right
to criticize me.

153
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,640
They can insult, mock, belittle me,
and say whatever they want!

154
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:06,560
Go ahead, say whatever you want!
I don't feel anything, Pun!

155
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:25,040
Ma'am. Ma'am.

156
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:27,360
Mr. Pun and Ms. Pie
are having a huge argument.

157
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,640
It's so loud,
it's even heard outside the house.

158
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,880
What?

159
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,480
- Let's go see.
- Yes.

160
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,720
Pie, what's going on?
Why are you acting like this?

161
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,280
Why can't we talk about it nicely?

162
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:41,560
- Will throwing a tantrum solve anything?
- Throwing a tantrum?

163
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,600
I've never thrown a tantrum, Pun.

164
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,120
I'm just protecting myself.

165
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,640
Honestly, I should have done this
a long time ago.

166
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,800
But I didn't
because I tried to be patient.

167
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:53,160
I stayed patient because I thought
things would get better!

168
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,800
<i>The patience in a relationship</i>
<i>has its limits.</i>

169
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,760
What we used to tolerate,

170
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,280
<i>eventually we don't want to anymore.</i>

171
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:07,000
When you don't want to tolerate it,
you have to find a way out!

172
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:15,080
Don't talk to me like that!

173
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,480
Oh my goodness!

174
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,040
What's going on?

175
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,680
What did you do, Pie?

176
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,360
Why is Pun this angry?

177
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,720
Mom, I need to talk to Pie alone.

178
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,560
Talking won't help.

179
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,080
Your wife isn't good for anything.

180
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:40,480
She just causes you stress.

181
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:44,120
What you just said, is it really right?

182
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,000
You still have to ask?

183
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:48,000
Can't you see his face?

184
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,160
It's obvious he's not happy.

185
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:23,920
If I'm the one making you unhappy,

186
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,520
then we shouldn't stay together.

187
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,640
Pie!

188
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,880
Pie!

189
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,120
- Where are you going?
- Pun!

190
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,000
- I won't let you go. Come back!
- Pun, don't!

191
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,920
- Stop! I won't let you go!
- Let her go.

192
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,360
- Pie!
- Just let her go.

193
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:45,080
Hold him tight. Hurry up.
Pun, listen to me.

194
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,600
Don't say anything right now.

195
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:52,680
If you're going to talk,
wait until you both cool down.

196
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,200
Trust me, okay?

197
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:23,480
Go get the staff and clean up the house.

198
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:24,720
- Quickly.
- Yes, ma'am.

199
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,960
Pie!

200
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,920
What happened? Did you and Pun argue?

201
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,600
Was it really that bad?

202
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:53,520
Are you really packing your things
to go stay with me?

203
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,600
- What happened, Pie?
- Mom.

204
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:57,800
I'm going to take a bath and sleep first.

205
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,720
I have to go out of town tomorrow.
I need to leave early.

206
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:01,880
Hey, Pie.

207
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:05,040
Tell me what happened with Pun first.
What did you argue about?

208
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,040
Pie.

209
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,000
Mom.

210
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,600
Please let me be.

211
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,120
Hello, Pun.

212
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:22,320
What's going on?
Why is Pie staying at my house?

213
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,160
We had an argument, Mom. It's my fault.

214
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:31,880
I'm stressed about Dad,
and I ended up taking it out on her.

215
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,840
Oh no!

216
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:38,880
Alright, I understand
that the situation with your dad is tough.

217
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:42,040
But don't forget,
Pie doesn't know anything about this.

218
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:46,200
Here's the plan. I'll talk to her for you.

219
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,040
Just calm down for now,
and you can talk tomorrow.

220
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,560
<i>Wait, no!</i>

221
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,720
She said she has to work
out of town tomorrow.

222
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,480
Let's talk another time, then.

223
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,720
Sure.

224
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,800
I'm sorry. Goodbye.

225
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,720
Pie, where are you?

226
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,600
Pie.

227
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:53,880
It's okay, sweetheart.

228
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,200
Don't cry, Pie.

229
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,840
Life in marriage is like this, you know.

230
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,520
There are arguments sometimes.

231
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:03,600
But you just have to talk,
adjust, and work things out.

232
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:05,760
And it will get better, okay?

233
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,040
It might not get better, Mom.

234
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,600
I've tried my best.

235
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:19,160
But it's just too much.

236
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:21,280
Well, it's okay.

237
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,400
If it's too much, take a break first.

238
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:25,040
When you've rested,

239
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:28,680
you can talk things through again,
and it will get better.

240
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,760
Pie.

241
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:35,640
Marriage isn't always smooth.

242
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:41,720
Once you work things out, talk it over,
everything will be okay.

243
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,240
Don't cry, sweetheart.

244
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,560
Hey, Pun!

245
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:09,200
How did you get here?

246
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:12,160
I had an argument with Pie.

247
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,080
About what?

248
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,000
It's something trivial.

249
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:27,160
I probably took out all my stress
from other things on her.

250
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,880
She ended up going back to her mom's.

251
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,960
I've never seen myself act like this.

252
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:01,680
I don't even know what happened.

253
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,760
It just exploded out of nowhere.

254
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,200
So how is Pie doing?

255
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,440
She's in shock, of course.

256
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,280
Did you blow up…

257
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,400
to the point of getting physical?

258
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:29,600
No, not like that.

259
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,920
I didn't hurt Pie physically.

260
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,240
But I still feel bad about it.

261
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,240
I know she has to work
out of town tomorrow.

262
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:49,880
Rok told me
it's just the two of them going.

263
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,160
I'm worried.

264
00:20:58,560 --> 00:20:59,920
I want you to help me out.

265
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,960
But Pie already has Rok, right?

266
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:08,760
Rok doesn't really know much.

267
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:11,040
It's just the two women going.
I'm worried.

268
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:14,520
You know the area better than they do,
since you're local.

269
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,160
Please.

270
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,600
Take care of Pie for me.

271
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:23,000
Why don't you go yourself?

272
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,800
I have something important to do.

273
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,720
Please help me feel at ease.

274
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:54,560
04:30
SUNDAY 3RD SEPTEMBER

275
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,080
ONE MINUTE

276
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:15,280
Here it is. Is this the one?

277
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,440
Not this one.

278
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,960
I called for the bigger one.

279
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:31,720
Hey, Win! How did you get here?

280
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,200
Pun told me to come.

281
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,200
So surprised.

282
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,720
What's the surprise?

283
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:45,520
Pun told me you booked the ticket for me.

284
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:48,600
He said I should fly to Chiang Mai,
then drive to Mae Hong Son.

285
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,560
Oh right, I completely forgot about that.

286
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:52,920
Rok.

287
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,040
You're terrible at lying. Try again.

288
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,280
Well.

289
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,280
Hey, here it is. This is the one.

290
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,800
Let's go. Get in the car.

291
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,080
Hurry up, Pie.

292
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:13,800
Mom!

293
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,040
Rok, help me!

294
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:19,160
Mom! Mom!

295
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,000
Mom!

296
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,680
Rok.

297
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:35,520
I'm so sorry.
You missed work because of me.

298
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,840
It's fine, Mom.

299
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:38,200
It wasn't my main job anyway.

300
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:40,160
I was just accompanying Pie.

301
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,760
You're more important.

302
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:43,000
That's sweet.

303
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,440
- Take it easy, Mom.
- Okay.

304
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:49,760
Who's here?

305
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:51,480
I'll be right back, Mom.

306
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,040
Okay, go check.

307
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,960
Who's here? Rok!

308
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,520
Krarok, Dad's here!

309
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:03,160
Dad!

310
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,200
- Hey!
- Dad!

311
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,920
You're back!

312
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,720
Come on.

313
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:14,640
Dad!

314
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:22,440
You said you were coming next week.
What happened?

315
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,120
Oh, come on. I missed you guys.

316
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,680
Can't I come earlier?

317
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,200
Dad, tell me the truth.

318
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:29,480
The stinky beans are perfect.

319
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:32,200
I wanted your mom to enjoy them,
so I swapped shifts with a friend.

320
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,320
So, where's Mom?

321
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,720
You didn't read the message?

322
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:37,880
I didn't turn on the internet.

323
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,760
No wonder you didn't know.

324
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:42,320
- What do you mean?
- Mom fell. The doctor says she needs rest.

325
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,680
She's in a cast at home.

326
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,520
Why tell me now?

327
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,960
Oh, shoot!

328
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:48,520
Mom, does it hurt a lot?

329
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:50,320
Dad's here!

330
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,720
Since when did you start
calling yourself that?

331
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,840
He's been watching
too many YouTube videos.

332
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:03,600
Mom.

333
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:05,640
That's so sad.

334
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,640
Looks like no more fun for you now.

335
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,160
‪What a shame.

336
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:12,800
I was going to take you on a date.
Such a shame.

337
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,680
Hey, don't worry.

338
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,840
I'll get you an electric wheelchair.

339
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:18,240
Oh, no need. You're overdoing it.

340
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:19,640
I'll be fine soon.

341
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:22,520
As for the date, we can have it at home.

342
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:26,600
- Want a date with me?
- You're so full of yourself!

343
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:29,120
You're the one
who came to see me, remember?

344
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:33,200
If I can't come see my wife,
where else should I go?

345
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:35,760
That was harsh, but true.

346
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,600
- Oh, it hurts.
- Does it hurt?

347
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:41,080
- It hurts.
- Take it easy.

348
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,720
THA PHAE GATE

349
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:46,240
Hey, how's your mom doing?

350
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:48,240
<i>She's okay.</i>

351
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:51,440
Her leg still hurts,
but she's got someone to comfort her.

352
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:52,920
Her husband came.

353
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,280
They're sitting there, all lovey-dovey.

354
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:57,520
Even at their age, they're still so sweet.

355
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,000
It makes me jealous.

356
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:01,120
You can't be jealous of your dad, can you?

357
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:04,720
Hey, let them be sweet. Come join me here.

358
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,720
Let's go together. What do you think?

359
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:09,520
It's fine. I don't
want to waste your time.

360
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:11,120
Plus, I want to spend time with Dad.

361
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,680
I don't often see him from down south.

362
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,720
<i>Rok!</i>

363
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:17,120
Come help me peel the stinky beans!

364
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:20,240
Okay, I'll be right there, boss.

365
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,040
I've gotta go now.

366
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,880
Dad's calling me.

367
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:26,240
You be nice to Win, okay?

368
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:28,200
Don't argue and mess up the work.

369
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:29,800
I'll try.

370
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:32,480
Bye.

371
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:41,160
Let's go.

372
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:45,240
Why not hire a driver to take us?
It'd be easier.

373
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:47,120
Easier for getting car sick, you mean.

374
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,960
If I don't drive, I'll throw up.

375
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:50,320
I feel sorry for myself.

376
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,440
Feel sorry for those
waiting for you to throw up.

377
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,920
You throw up
more than a pregnant woman does.

378
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,320
You remember that?

379
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,800
Hurry up. I don't want to get there late.

380
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:24,920
CHIANG MAI BUS TERMINAL

381
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,280
Is Grandma Khamman not here?

382
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:26,680
Yes, she went up the mountain.

383
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:28,800
She goes back and forth.
She has two houses.

384
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:30,880
One here and one up on the mountain.

385
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:33,840
She went up there just the other day.

386
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,520
Did you two make an appointment with her?

387
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,880
Yes, I called to schedule it yesterday.

388
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,440
She probably forgot.

389
00:28:40,520 --> 00:28:43,040
She gets confused sometimes,
so it's uncertain.

390
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:43,920
Yes.

391
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,520
Can we drive up to see Grandma
on the mountain?

392
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:47,720
Are you from the north?

393
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,720
Yes, my mom's from Chiang Rai.

394
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:52,000
We're from the same place then.

395
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:55,600
You know what?
I'll have my partner drive you.

396
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:58,080
It's difficult to drive up the mountain.

397
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,520
No need to go up yourself.

398
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:02,400
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

399
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,600
You can take the money
for gas and travel expenses.

400
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,680
It's okay. No need.

401
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:08,640
Don't worry about money.
Don't talk about it.

402
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,520
- I'll have my partner take you.
- Thank you.

403
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,640
Honey! Honey!

404
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:13,840
Come here for a second.

405
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,040
Yes?

406
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,240
Can you drive them up to the mountain?

407
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:21,080
To Grandma Khamman's house.

408
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:22,000
Sure.

409
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:23,560
Sorry to bother you.

410
00:29:23,640 --> 00:29:25,040
It's fine. No problem.

411
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:29,120
PUN

412
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:31,600
Excuse me a bit. I'll be right back.

413
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,760
I'm really sorry to bother you.

414
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:41,640
Yes, Pun?

415
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:44,720
How's it going, Win?

416
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,520
Have you found any information?

417
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:47,840
I've just arrived.

418
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:50,040
But Grandma moved up to the mountain.

419
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,600
I'll have the locals
take me up to see her.

420
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:57,600
And what about Pie?

421
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:02,400
Pie…

422
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,960
She's focused on her work, like usual.

423
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:07,120
Okay.

424
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:09,600
I'm feeling less worried now.

425
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:12,360
Thanks a lot, Win.

426
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:14,880
I'll call for an update later.

427
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,400
Take good care of Pie and Rok.

428
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,200
Yes, Pun.

429
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,840
Hey!

430
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,040
Stop the car. I'm gonna puke!

431
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:02,560
I can't stop here!

432
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,040
Hold it in for now!

433
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:06,800
Wait, hold on. Don't throw up yet.

434
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:08,640
Here.

435
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:17,000
Take whatever you need.

436
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,040
Take some pills.

437
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:39,200
Water.

438
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:42,360
I've got gum and mints too.

439
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,280
Help yourself.

440
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:44,680
Why do you have everything?

441
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:46,600
For people who don't have anything.

442
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:50,760
Why are you smiling?

443
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,080
You're even more prepared now.

444
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,600
I brought it for Rok, not for anyone else.

445
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:03,640
But seeing your condition, I had to share.

446
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,400
You don't have to take it.

447
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:08,720
I'll take it.

448
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:53,920
- Rok.
- Yes?

449
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:57,000
Leave some garlic skin on.
Your mom likes it that way.

450
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:58,040
Got it.

451
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,360
- Dad.
- What's up?

452
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:04,200
You work far from Mom.

453
00:33:04,280 --> 00:33:05,640
Sometimes you don't meet for months.

454
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,160
Do you have a mistress?

455
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,360
Plenty.

456
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:12,760
Does our house have a ghost or something?

457
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,640
Come on, what for?

458
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,400
Why would I have one?

459
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:20,320
I don't go looking for trouble
or create problems for myself.

460
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,280
Why do you think that way?

461
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:26,160
My life's good right now.

462
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:29,160
I have a lovely wife,
a beautiful daughter,

463
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:32,240
a house, and enough money
to live comfortably.

464
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:33,880
When I'm tired from work,

465
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:36,520
I just call you and your mom,
and I feel better.

466
00:33:37,320 --> 00:33:40,200
I finish work,
have dinner, and sleep well.

467
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:43,360
My life right now, it's perfect.

468
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:46,320
So, what's wrong with having a mistress?

469
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,880
It's wrong in every way.

470
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,520
Having a mistress means what?

471
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:52,520
Your wife finds out, you argue, break up,

472
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,120
and the kid feels bad.

473
00:33:54,200 --> 00:33:59,000
You come home tired
and have to cover up the mistake you made.

474
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,040
What a mess.

475
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:04,320
Sure, it might be exciting at first.

476
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,040
With that kind of thing.

477
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,159
But the trouble follows you like a shadow.

478
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:10,120
I don't need that. Not worth it.

479
00:34:12,560 --> 00:34:14,040
Dad, you're so cool.

480
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,760
Mom is so lucky to have you as a husband.

481
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:21,400
And I'm really lucky to have you as a dad.

482
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,360
You're my darling girl.

483
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,000
Dad, do you know?

484
00:34:25,080 --> 00:34:27,520
Every one of my exes
has plenty of mistresses.

485
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:29,199
No one thinks like you do.

486
00:34:30,199 --> 00:34:32,280
Don't worry about that, sweetheart.

487
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:34,600
With things like this,
if it's meant to be,

488
00:34:34,679 --> 00:34:35,880
it will come naturally.

489
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:39,679
As for all those bad people in the past,
just cut ties and move on.

490
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:46,320
You're dressed a bit differently today.
Is this a new style?

491
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:48,639
Come on, tell me. What's going on?

492
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,920
Nothing right now.

493
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:52,600
But if things become clear,

494
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:55,480
I'll bring him to introduce to you
at your work site down south.

495
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:57,920
Bring him! I'm waiting for him!

496
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:01,480
Anyway, I'll go call him now.

497
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:07,160
You were this small.

498
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:09,200
And now look at you.

499
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,000
The love life of young people.

500
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:22,880
MR. SHOHEI

501
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:28,480
<i>Sorry, the number that you've dialed</i>
<i>cannot be connected at this time.</i>

502
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:30,720
Looks like you're out of range.

503
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,280
<i>How's everything?</i>

504
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,720
<i>How many rounds did you two argue?</i>

505
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:42,480
<i>Anyway, take care of yourself.</i>

506
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:45,200
<i>I'm worried.</i>

507
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,920
Why isn't he back yet?

508
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,080
Pun!

509
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:08,560
Hey.

510
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,760
How's your wife?

511
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,960
She's not coming back, right?

512
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:14,560
Mom.

513
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:17,160
Pie's just upset with me.
We haven't broken up yet.

514
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,760
Mom.

515
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:25,360
I just want you to be happy.

516
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:28,360
Be with a wife who's suitable,
who matches your status.

517
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:30,080
That's all I want.

518
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,560
Is Dad not back yet?

519
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:41,600
Not yet. Maybe he'll come back next week.

520
00:36:42,120 --> 00:36:44,200
Who knows how far he's gotten
with his spiritual journey.

521
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,480
Let's eat. Come on.

522
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:51,240
Tian, serve the rice.

523
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,160
Come on. Time to eat.

524
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:56,000
I'll handle it myself.

525
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,600
All the dishes look delicious.

526
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,440
Look, we've got your favorite too.

527
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:04,440
This pig's trotter is really tasty.

528
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:06,800
Thanks, Pun.

529
00:37:16,960 --> 00:37:17,880
Here.

530
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:28,120
- Mom.
- Yes?

531
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:32,080
Have you ever thought about…

532
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:36,000
what you'd do if Dad ever cheated on you?

533
00:37:37,720 --> 00:37:39,080
Why are you asking?

534
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,440
Is your wife cheating on you?

535
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:47,040
No, Mom. It's not about Pie.

536
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,160
I'm just curious.

537
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:52,880
There's been news lately
about celebrities cheating.

538
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:57,760
So I was wondering,
if something like this happened,

539
00:37:58,720 --> 00:37:59,920
what would you do?

540
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:06,600
I don't know. I've never thought about it.

541
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,400
Because your dad would never cheat on me.

542
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:16,200
Why are you so sure of that?

543
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:18,920
Pun.

544
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:21,080
Look at me.

545
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:23,200
Look at this house.

546
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:24,680
Look at our family.

547
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:27,120
Look at everything we have.

548
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,560
Where would your dad
find a woman better than me?

549
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:31,040
Nowhere.

550
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,920
But if he did, I'd be shocked.

551
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:43,040
I'd never think
someone we love could betray us.

552
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,200
And I'd be the most disappointed.

553
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:50,720
Loving someone means you'll get hurt more.

554
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:52,280
That's normal.

555
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:57,400
But I trust your dad.

556
00:38:58,280 --> 00:39:00,440
He'd never betray me.

557
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,600
Now, let's eat.

558
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:34,960
MUNGMINK

559
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,040
Yes, Mink?

560
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:46,000
Has Pie moved back to her own place?

561
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:51,360
Did Mom call you to tell you about it?

562
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:53,680
Yes.

563
00:39:54,240 --> 00:39:55,640
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

564
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,280
She told you about something unimportant.

565
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,680
No need to apologize.

566
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:02,880
I'm happy to listen.

567
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,480
Are you okay, Pun?

568
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:07,840
How are you doing?

569
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,800
That's a big sigh.

570
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:20,440
If you say you're okay,
I'd say you're lying.

571
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:25,040
My wife asked to go back to her mom's.

572
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:26,480
Who could be okay with that?

573
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:32,440
Well, let me say this again.

574
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:36,640
If you ever need to vent
or talk about anything,

575
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,880
I'm always here to listen.

576
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:41,680
Because in the past,

577
00:40:41,760 --> 00:40:44,280
<i>you've helped me feel better many times.</i>

578
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:47,200
I'd like to return the favor.

579
00:40:48,120 --> 00:40:49,880
I want to see you happy.

580
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,680
Thank you so much, Mink.

581
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:55,560
Good night.

582
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,840
Good night.

583
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:24,240
Grandma Khamman
just went to bed a little while ago.

584
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:25,760
Let's talk tomorrow morning.

585
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:27,640
For now, let's rest.

586
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,480
I'll take you to another house.

587
00:41:29,560 --> 00:41:31,880
Not far from here.
That house has a guest room.

588
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:33,120
- Follow me.
- Yes

589
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:38,880
Are you two married?

590
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:41,120
No, we're not.

591
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:45,280
We're coworkers.

592
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:49,000
Good thing I checked.
Almost had you two sharing a room.

593
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,360
Come on. Let's go.

594
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:01,640
Mom, I'm going too!

595
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:03,920
Stay here. I'll be right back.

596
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:44,000
Enjoy your meal!

597
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:45,440
- Thank you.
- Alright.

598
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:47,320
- Enjoy.
- Kaew, join us for the meal.

599
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:49,160
I've eaten already. Feel free.

600
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:50,880
- Thank you.
- No problem.

601
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:35,000
If I'm sitting here and you can't eat,
just let me know.

602
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,200
Quiet, just eat. No need to talk so much.

603
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:02,480
Pie, can we be friends?

604
00:45:02,560 --> 00:45:03,520
No.

605
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:07,040
You don't even think about it?

606
00:45:08,120 --> 00:45:09,000
No.

607
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:21,880
Why are you smiling?

608
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:27,160
You're afraid of being friends with me,

609
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:29,640
so you deny it without even thinking.

610
00:45:31,720 --> 00:45:34,320
I'm not afraid. Why would I be afraid?

611
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,600
That's for you to answer.

612
00:45:38,480 --> 00:45:40,560
Why are you afraid
of being friends with me?

613
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:53,400
Why did you walk away?

614
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,320
See? You're afraid.

615
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:00,440
I'm not afraid.

616
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:11,320
Good, I don't want you to be afraid.

617
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:23,400
Pie.

618
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:32,960
We can be friends. Trust me.

619
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:38,080
We'll be good friends

620
00:46:38,880 --> 00:46:40,160
and wish the best for each other.

621
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:48,880
Whenever you see me as a friend,

622
00:46:50,320 --> 00:46:52,040
you can talk to me

623
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:54,480
about anything.

624
00:48:58,800 --> 00:49:00,400
Uncle Dech sent you here?

625
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:01,440
Yes, Grandma.

626
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:06,520
Dech who?

627
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,000
Well, Grandma's getting older.

628
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:13,440
Some days she forgets things.

629
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:15,520
Try talking about Uncle Dech a lot.

630
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:16,880
That could help her recall.

631
00:49:17,720 --> 00:49:18,720
Okay.

632
00:49:20,840 --> 00:49:23,000
Grandma.

633
00:49:23,080 --> 00:49:25,960
Do you remember Mrs. Sangdao?

634
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:27,640
She's Uncle Dech's mother.

635
00:49:28,240 --> 00:49:29,280
Mr. Dechnarong.

636
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:31,760
You used to help her out.

637
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:33,800
I used to help her?

638
00:49:33,880 --> 00:49:35,240
Yes.

639
00:49:39,440 --> 00:49:40,280
I don't remember.

640
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:52,760
Grandma!

641
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:55,960
Grandma, where are you going?

642
00:49:56,040 --> 00:49:57,520
I'm going to feed the pigs.

643
00:49:58,760 --> 00:50:00,200
Feed the pigs?

644
00:50:01,040 --> 00:50:03,560
Normally, at this time,
she'd go to feed the pigs.

645
00:50:03,640 --> 00:50:05,200
So she would walk there.

646
00:50:05,280 --> 00:50:06,440
It's like this.

647
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:08,480
Whether she remembers or not,
we just have to hope.

648
00:50:08,560 --> 00:50:11,480
Follow her. Maybe she'll remember.

649
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:13,760
- Okay, Kaew. Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

650
00:50:13,840 --> 00:50:15,840
Grandma!

651
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:36,080
Are you hungry?

652
00:50:36,160 --> 00:50:38,960
Come on. Let's eat.

653
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:40,440
Eat up!

654
00:50:40,520 --> 00:50:42,240
Grandma.

655
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:46,480
Uncle Dech said
that when you were younger,

656
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:50,040
you often helped his mom
pick out beautiful fabrics.

657
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:51,160
Is that right?

658
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:53,360
Come on. Eat a lot!

659
00:50:53,440 --> 00:50:55,960
You can get big and strong.

660
00:50:57,840 --> 00:50:58,920
This isn't going anywhere.

661
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:00,440
She's only talking to the pigs.

662
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:01,720
Yeah, right.

663
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:04,840
‪Yeah, like that.

664
00:51:04,920 --> 00:51:05,960
Here's what I'll do.

665
00:51:06,040 --> 00:51:08,200
I'll video call Uncle Dech
and have him talk to her.

666
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:09,640
Maybe that'll help.

667
00:51:09,720 --> 00:51:12,280
I heard from Kaew
that there's some signal around here.

668
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:14,040
You stay and talk to her for now.

669
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:21,000
Grandma.

670
00:51:21,520 --> 00:51:25,160
Pie is going to get Uncle Dech
to talk to you, okay?

671
00:51:25,240 --> 00:51:26,240
Alright?

672
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:33,520
Yeah, just eat.

673
00:51:33,600 --> 00:51:34,440
Okay?

674
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:38,720
Grandma.

675
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:41,320
Let me do it. You go rest.

676
00:51:41,400 --> 00:51:42,400
Okay.

677
00:51:42,480 --> 00:51:43,680
Be careful, Grandma.

678
00:51:45,680 --> 00:51:46,520
Take it easy.

679
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:48,280
Alright, Grandma.

680
00:51:48,920 --> 00:51:51,240
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

681
00:51:52,240 --> 00:51:53,760
Make sure it eats a lot.

682
00:51:54,280 --> 00:51:55,160
Okay.

683
00:51:58,520 --> 00:52:00,160
Talk to it a little.

684
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:04,760
- Talk to who?
- Talk to the pig.

685
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:06,440
Talk to the pig?

686
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:09,680
Tell it to eat a lot.

687
00:52:15,960 --> 00:52:16,880
Sure, let's do this.

688
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:22,600
Grandma, should I speak
in standard Thai or the Northern dialect?

689
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:24,160
Use the Northern dialect with it.

690
00:52:24,240 --> 00:52:25,480
- With the pig, right?
- Yeah.

691
00:52:25,560 --> 00:52:26,960
Talk to it so it understands.

692
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:31,240
Alright, pig!

693
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:33,440
Hey, eat up!

694
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:36,040
Grandma made this for you.

695
00:52:38,120 --> 00:52:39,840
Come on, big boy.

696
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:40,920
- Eat a lot.
- Yeah.

697
00:52:41,000 --> 00:52:44,160
- A pig has to be fat. Eat a lot!
- Yeah.

698
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:45,560
- That's right.
- Feed the small one too.

699
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:47,800
- The small one too? Got it.
- Yes, that one.

700
00:52:47,880 --> 00:52:48,720
You bit me?

701
00:52:50,280 --> 00:52:51,480
Good job.

702
00:52:51,560 --> 00:52:53,880
A pig has to be fat, or it's a waste.

703
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:56,120
Eat up, little one.

704
00:52:56,640 --> 00:52:57,480
Here.

705
00:52:58,440 --> 00:53:00,320
Yeah, eat more.

706
00:53:01,880 --> 00:53:04,520
Just like that. Pigs have to be like this.

707
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:06,640
You chubby! Chubby pig.

708
00:53:14,600 --> 00:53:16,040
There's no signal.

709
00:53:17,200 --> 00:53:18,640
Thank you.

710
00:53:18,720 --> 00:53:19,560
Sure.

711
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:31,880
Come on, eat!

712
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:33,960
Hurry up!

713
00:53:34,040 --> 00:53:35,680
A pig has to eat a lot to get big.

714
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:37,640
That way, Grandma will be happy.

715
00:53:37,720 --> 00:53:40,160
Yeah, just like that.

716
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:43,880
Big and fat, Grandma likes it.

717
00:53:44,560 --> 00:53:46,400
Am I good at this?
Am I good at feeding pigs?

718
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:47,600
Yeah.

719
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:48,880
Good job.

720
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:50,640
It will get even bigger, Grandma.

721
00:53:51,440 --> 00:53:52,800
Just wait and see.

722
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:54,360
Here.

723
00:53:59,160 --> 00:54:02,760
You really do talk to the pigs,
just like Mr. Dech.

724
00:54:02,840 --> 00:54:05,000
Mr. Dech likes to talk to dogs and cats.

725
00:54:07,880 --> 00:54:08,720
Grandma.

726
00:54:10,200 --> 00:54:11,800
Grandma.

727
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:13,840
Do you remember Uncle Dech now?

728
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:16,480
How could I forget?

729
00:54:16,560 --> 00:54:18,400
I've known him since he was a kid.

730
00:54:19,200 --> 00:54:22,320
Mr. Dech is a good talker,
just like this young man.

731
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:24,560
So, who are you to Mr. Dech?

732
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:27,480
Grandma, my name is Pie.

733
00:54:27,560 --> 00:54:29,680
Uncle Dech asked me to interview you
about the fabrics.

734
00:54:29,760 --> 00:54:32,480
I heard he already contacted you.
Do you remember?

735
00:54:33,680 --> 00:54:35,600
How could I not remember?

736
00:54:35,680 --> 00:54:38,000
I remember.

737
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:41,440
Mr. Dech is opening a fabric museum.

738
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:42,760
Yes, that's right.

739
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:45,560
Come on. I've got something to show you.

740
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:47,040
- Okay, sure.
- Alright.

741
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:48,680
- Please get up slowly.
- Okay.

742
00:54:48,760 --> 00:54:50,080
- Take it easy.
- Yes.

743
00:54:50,160 --> 00:54:52,120
- I've got it ready.
- Alright.

744
00:54:53,440 --> 00:54:54,560
Grandma remembers now!

745
00:54:58,120 --> 00:54:59,920
You finally smiled at me!

746
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:04,120
Grandma.

747
00:55:04,200 --> 00:55:07,000
- Wait for me! I'll help.
- I shouldn't have said anything.

748
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:09,800
Well done, pig!

749
00:55:09,880 --> 00:55:11,040
See you later!

750
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:13,840
Grandma, I'm coming.

751
00:55:14,440 --> 00:55:15,480
Let's go!

752
00:55:19,960 --> 00:55:22,000
This is the fabric logbook.

753
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:23,280
Mr. Dech's mother asked me

754
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:25,560
to keep track of everything
since I was young,

755
00:55:25,640 --> 00:55:27,720
when I used to help buy fabrics.

756
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:30,640
It's all written down,
what kind of fabric it is,

757
00:55:30,720 --> 00:55:33,440
where it's from, how it's woven.

758
00:55:33,520 --> 00:55:36,200
This way, we won't forget when we sell it.

759
00:55:38,440 --> 00:55:42,240
Wow, Grandma, this is really detailed!

760
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:44,440
Yes, I wrote it all down for selling.

761
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:46,720
But she never sold a single piece.

762
00:55:47,440 --> 00:55:48,880
She kept them all.

763
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:52,120
So, which fabrics
is Mr. Dech going to showcase?

764
00:55:53,440 --> 00:55:54,800
- Just a second.
- Okay.

765
00:55:55,320 --> 00:55:57,200
I've prepared some pictures. Here you go.

766
00:55:57,280 --> 00:56:00,080
- You can look through them, Grandma.
- Alright.

767
00:56:00,160 --> 00:56:01,440
This is what we will showcase.

768
00:56:01,520 --> 00:56:03,120
Actually, there are more.

769
00:56:03,200 --> 00:56:05,880
You can look at this album first.
I'll go get the rest for you.

770
00:56:05,960 --> 00:56:07,960
I'll go get it. You wait here.

771
00:56:11,120 --> 00:56:12,760
‪-Right here.
‪-Yes.

772
00:56:25,760 --> 00:56:27,560
- Are you alright?
- That must hurt a lot.

773
00:56:31,240 --> 00:56:32,320
Are you okay?

774
00:56:34,880 --> 00:56:36,600
I'm fine. It's okay.

775
00:56:36,680 --> 00:56:37,920
I'll be right back.

776
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:45,600
Back to work. I'll be right back.

777
00:56:49,400 --> 00:56:50,560
Oh my!

778
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:53,320
Seems like you're only good
at talking to pigs!

779
00:57:14,040 --> 00:57:15,200
I think Pie has someone else.

780
00:57:16,840 --> 00:57:18,680
<i>People can have secrets,</i>

781
00:57:19,320 --> 00:57:22,000
<i>even when you're always together.</i>

782
00:57:22,600 --> 00:57:24,520
<i>If they want to hide something,</i>

783
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:27,200
<i>they'll find a way</i>
<i>to get away with it, surprisingly.</i>

784
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:30,960
<i>No matter where I stand,</i>

785
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:35,760
<i>I'll always be by your side.</i>

786
00:57:38,080 --> 00:57:40,120
<i>No matter how much you change,</i>

787
00:57:41,480 --> 00:57:43,400
<i>I'm the one who stays the same.</i>

788
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:46,960
I'm not the perfect woman
who's never made a mistake.

789
00:57:47,040 --> 00:57:50,200
I'm just a broken girl
who once got pregnant, Mom!

790
00:57:52,560 --> 00:57:54,600
If she still hasn't told me
what's in her heart,

791
00:57:54,680 --> 00:57:56,680
the secret she's hiding,

792
00:57:56,760 --> 00:57:58,680
I'll find the truth myself.

793
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,960
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
